{"id":"1904.05371","submitter":"Baptiste Louf","authors":"Baptiste Louf","title":"Simple formulas for constellations and bipartite maps with prescribed\n  degrees","comments":"16 pages, 4 figures, extended abstract in FPSAC 2019, to appear in\n  CJM","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.4153/S0008414X19000555","report-no":null,"categories":"math.CO","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We obtain simple quadratic recurrence formulas counting bipartite maps on\nsurfaces with prescribed degrees (in particular, $2k$-angulations), and\nconstellations. These formulas are the fastest known way of computing these\nnumbers. Our work is a natural extension of previous works on integrable\nhierarchies (2-Toda and KP), namely the Pandharipande recursion for Hurwitz\nnumbers (proven by Okounkov and simplified by Dubrovin-Yang-Zagier), as well as\nformulas for several models of maps (Goulden-Jackson, Carrell-Chapuy,\nKazarian-Zograf). As for those formulas, a bijective interpretation is still to\nbe found. We also include a formula for monotone simple Hurwitz numbers derived\nin the same fashion. These formulas also play a key role in subsequent work of\nthe author with T. Budzinski establishing the hyperbolic local limit of random\nbipartite maps of large genus.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 10 Apr 2019 18:01:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 31 Oct 2019 17:18:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-12-11"}
