, the effect of $s<s_{blow}$ grains remains limited in the\nspectra, in spite of the fact that they dominate the system's geometrical cross\nsection. We also find that, for all considered cases, the halo of small (bound\nand unbound) grains that extends far beyond the main disc contributes to\n$\\sim50$% of the flux up to $\\lambda\\sim50\\mu$m wavelengths.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 10 Apr 2019 19:12:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-06-12"}
